// D1.0 net-expansion: integer divide-by-zero divergence (unmeasured pre-D1.0).
// Interpreter: clean RUNTIME ERROR "division by zero" (ops.rs guard), exit 1.
// JIT: no guard — Cranelift's sdiv trap reaches hardware and the process dies
// with STATUS_ILLEGAL_INSTRUCTION (0xC000001D). The divisor is a variable so
// the zero reaches runtime instead of semantic analysis (same trick as
// t_oob_array_read). Fix lands in the JIT memory-safety gate (D1.2 guards);
// remove the .jit_known_unsound marker then.
a: t32 = 5
b: t32 = 0
print(a / b)
